    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Regarded as Inferior to Mission Service</strong>&mdash;What an important work! And yet we hear mothers sighing for missionary work! If they could only go to some foreign country, they would feel that they were doing something worth while. But to take up the daily duties of the home life and carry them forward seems to them like an exhausting and thankless task.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">3<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 7-9-1901\" data-link=\"821.20596\">The Review and Herald, July 9, 1901</span>.</span></a></sup>",
